%N A394671 Power tower of ascending prime factors of n with multiplicity.
%C A394671 The base of the exponent tower is the smallest prime factor of n, and the top exponent is the largest.
%e A394671 The prime factorization of 18 in ascending order is 2*3*3; therefore, a(18) = 2^3^3 = 2^27 = 134217728.
%t A394671 A394671[n_] := Power @@ Flatten[ConstantArray @@@ FactorInteger[n]];
